{"title":"Hope Tech add to eMTB parts line feat. new 2.3mm V4 lightning bolt brake rotors","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/03/hope-tech-add-to-emtb-parts-line-feat-new-2-3mm-v4-lightning-bolt-brake-rotors/","date":1614771860000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>British mountain bike manufacturers, Hope Technology, have added a couple new items to their ebike parts list. We take a look at the new 2.3mm thick V4 brake rotor with lightning bolt cut-outs, plus a new CNC machined head unit mount for the Bosch Kiox system.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb.jpg\" alt=\"hope tech v4 brake rotor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"845\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-297x209.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-800x563.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-120x85.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-768x541.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-696x490.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-1068x752.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-596x420.jpg 596w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-100x70.jpg 100w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-297x209.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-800x563.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-120x85.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-768x541.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-696x490.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-1068x752.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-596x420.jpg 596w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/hope-tech-v4-brake-rotor-emtb-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>The intention of the V4 brake disc rotor from Hope couldn’t be clearer, thanks to the lightning bolt shapes cut out of the braking surface. At 2.3mm thick, it is Hope Tech’s thickest brake rotor, designed to manage the additional heat generated when braking to slow down heav